</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,153,899]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,801,827]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" box="[323,495,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenis">
<emphasis box="[323,495,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Ceroptres lenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
emerged from a mix of galls stored inside the same breeding box: a tuberous twig gall, a leaf spherical velvety reddish gall and some leaf small spherical galls (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1136,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[251,1336,166,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[251,1336,166,1733]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 18. Some of the galls mentioned in this study: a) an undescribed species of Andricus (ref. 069); b) Sphaeroteras nr pulchripennis (ref. 103); c) Dros perlentum (ref. 123); d) Neuroterus eugeros (ref. 182); e) Andricus georgei (ref. 206); f) unknown leaf gall of Neuroterus (ref. 225); g) unknown leaf spherical gall (ref. 266); h) Andricus sphaericus (ref. 303); i) Andricus sphaericus (ref. 307); j) Andricus group georgei (ref. 312); k) Melikaiella amphibolensis (ref. 338); l) an undescribed species of Andricus on leaves (ref. P015); m) Atrusca sp. (ref. P149); n) unknown (P225); o) unknown undetachable leaf gall (ref. P233); p) unknown gall inside secondary leaf nerves (ref. P307); q) Atrusca pictor (ref. P322); r) Atrusca sp. (ref. P328); s) unknown (ref. 2B10, 13B6); t) unknown, a mix of galls (ref. 2840); u) unknown leaf petiole gall (ref. P366); v) unknown twig gall (ref. P308)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772874/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1098,1136,837,863]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="t" value="18.0">18t</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Hence, we are unable to determine from which of these galls the new species emerged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
